{
  "Adrenaline Junkie": {
    "type": [
      "Physical",
      "Thrill"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The bridge was out. A thirty-meter gap yawned over a river choked with collapsed rubble and rusted rebar. The squad stopped to assess. SOP-II did not stop.</em></p>
            <p>"SOP-II, wait... we need to find another..."</p>
            <p><em>She was already sprinting, boots hammering the fractured concrete. She launched off the broken edge, sailed across the gap, hit the other side in a roll, and popped up grinning, bits of gravel in her hair.</em></p>
            <p>"It's fine! The landing's soft-ish!"</p>
            <p>"That was a <em>thirty-meter gap</em>."</p>
            <p>"I know! Come on, you guys are gonna love it!"</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can risk your life without consideration or hesitation, even if the potential consequences are obvious and dire.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to risk your life (such as resisting a critical strike), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Ammosexual": {
    "type": [
      "Mental"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The burst stitched across the rooftop and the whole squad fell flat on the ground, concrete dust pelting their backs. The commander looked to the side, and one T-doll had stars in her eyes.</em></p>
            <p>"MG-42! It's an MG-42! Seven-point-nine-two Mauser, roller-locked, recoil-operated, twelve-hundred rounds per minute-"</p>
            <p>"<strong>Remi.</strong> It's shooting at us."</p>
            <p><em>A pause. Another burst tore through the air above them.</em></p>
            <p>"I know, isn't it awesome?"</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You have an extensive knowlege of firearms that most would call concering, and can easily identify the manufacturer and country of origin of any firearm you come across in the field.</li>
                <li>After interacting with a new weapon for the first time in any capacity (even being shot at with it), you lose three strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Animal Companion": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>After a long mission, the squad was resting at the base. Most of the T-dolls went off to mantain their weapons and recharge, but one remained in the lounge, playing with a cat, while another observed.</em></p>
            <p>"You're always playing with that cat, where'd you even find it?"</p>
            <p>"It followed us home after we found it on the street. I guess it just really likes me."</p>
            <p>"Weird."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>A small, mundane animal of some kind has attached itself to you. Choose one silhouette 0 or 1 animal, it follows you around wherever you go and acts as your companion. It can be convinced to do what you want, but might need incentives (usually food) to perform a difficult task.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to interact with an animal, you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Attention": {
    "type": [
      "Social"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The squad gathered in the briefing room, waiting for the commander to arrive. C-93 had rearranged all the chairs so that one sat slightly elevated at the front, facing the others.</em></p>
            <p>"C-93, what are you doing? That's not your seat."</p>
            <p>"Of course it's not my seat. It's my <em>stage</em>. I've prepared a tactical presentation."</p>
            <p>"...We don't have a mission yet."</p>
            <p>"Exactly! So everyone's free to watch. I even made slides."</p>
            <p><em>She held up a series of hand-drawn posters, each one featuring herself in increasingly dramatic poses.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>At the start of each scene, you can always determine the most effective way to gain the attention of those around you.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to capture someone’s attention (such as a check to draw a crowd with a daring move), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Celebrations": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Hedonic"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The base's annual morale event had been planned for weeks, but the turnout was low. Most dolls had drifted back to their quarters. Then UMP9 arrived with a portable speaker, three cases of supplies she'd "requisitioned" from logistics, and a grin that spelled trouble.</em></p>
            <p>"Nine, the party's basically over."</p>
            <p>"No it isn't. It hasn't started yet." <em>She cranked the volume.</em> "Someone go get 45. Tell her I said it's mandatory fun."</p>
            <p><em>Within the hour, the lounge was packed.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can always find the best activities at any celebration or gathering, and you never have trouble finding someone specific in a crowded place.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to interact at a celebration (such as a check to determine where clandestine dealings are happening at a crowded event or ensure a guest has a good time), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Charity": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>It was well past midnight when the commander passed by the café. The lights were still on. Inside, Springfield was wrapping a small package, a fresh muffin and a handwritten note tucked inside.</em></p>
            <p>"Springfield? It's almost 0200."</p>
            <p>"Oh, commander. I heard Galil's been having trouble adjusting after her transfer. I thought something warm might help her feel welcome."</p>
            <p>"You've already made six of those tonight."</p>
            <p><em>Springfield smiled, tying the ribbon with practiced fingers.</em></p>
            <p>"There are six dolls who could use a little kindness right now."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Your charitable nature makes those who have witnessed or heard of your generosity more likely to accept your reasonable requests for aid, even if giving you aid does not directly benefit the other party.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to help someone (such as check to provide aid or comfort), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Coffee": {
    "type": [
      "Mental",
      "Hedonic"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>WA2000 stood behind the counter of the empty café, measuring beans with a scale she'd brought from her own quarters. Springfield watched from the doorway with quiet amusement.</em></p>
            <p>"You know you're welcome to use the house blend."</p>
            <p>"Your house blend is over-roasted by at least thirty seconds. I can taste the char." <em>She adjusted the grinder by a single click.</em> "And your water temperature is two degrees too high. It's not complicated."</p>
            <p>"You could just ask me to make it differently."</p>
            <p>"I could. But then it wouldn't be right." <em>The kettle whistled. She poured in a slow, precise spiral, and for a few seconds, the furrow between her brows disappeared entirely.</em></p>
            <p><em>Springfield said nothing. She knew better than to interrupt the only moment in the day when WA2000 looked at peace.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can identify regional variations in coffee and tea, and you know a great deal about the process of preparing them. In the field, you can acquire natural ingredients to brew effective beverages with relative ease.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving coffee or tea (such as a check to brew a restorative blend with medicinal properties or prepare a drink that helps the recipients relax and reflect), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Collecting": {
    "type": [
      "Mental",
      "Reflective"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>SOP-II's quarters were... curated. That was the charitable word for it. Shelves lined with salvaged components, enemy optics, servo motors, and things that had once been attached to Sangvis Ferri units. Each one labeled with a date and location in her careful handwriting.</em></p>
            <p>"SOP, is that a Ringleader's voice modulator?"</p>
            <p>"Executioner's! From the raid on Sector 8. See the scoring on the housing? That's from when I..."</p>
            <p>"I don't need to know how you got it."</p>
            <p>"But that's the best part!"</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You are a compulsive collector. You always notice items of interest that others would overlook, and you can recall the exact provenance of every item in your collection.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to find, acquire, or catalog an interesting item (such as a check to scavenge useful components from wreckage or identify the origin of an unusual artifact), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Commerce": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Mental"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The vendor wanted six hundred for the parts. Stechkin wanted to pay two hundred. Twenty minutes later, she walked away with the parts, three hundred credits still in her pocket, and the vendor somehow feeling like he'd won.</em></p>
            <p>"How do you do that?" the commander asked.</p>
            <p>"Do what?"</p>
            <p>"Make people feel good about losing money."</p>
            <p><em>Stechkin counted her credits with a speed that bordered on affectionate.</em> "He didn't lose money, commander. He lost <em>less</em> money than he expected to. That's practically the same as profit. It's all about framing."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You always know the fair market value of any item or service, and you can haggle effectively in any market, bazaar, or back-alley deal. People who trade with you walk away satisfied even when the math doesn't favor them.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving trade, negotiation, or financial assessment (such as a check to haggle for a better price or appraise the value of salvaged goods), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Communal Meals": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal",
      "Hedonic"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The mission had gone badly. No casualties, but everyone was rattled. The squad filed back into the Elmo in silence. Springfield was already in the galley, and the smell hit them before they rounded the corner: something warm, rich, and entirely too good for what should have been a ration night.</em></p>
            <p>"Springfield, where did you get fresh vegetables?"</p>
            <p>"I have my sources. Sit down, all of you. Nobody debriefs on an empty stomach."</p>
            <p><em>Nobody argued. Within twenty minutes, the silence had turned into murmuring, then conversation, then something that almost sounded like laughter. Springfield refilled bowls without being asked and said nothing, but she was smiling.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You know how to prepare a hearty, comforting meal in a communal setting, even with limited ingredients. Because of the strong associations, sharing a meal you've prepared helps you recall memories connected to the people you've shared food with before.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving the preparation of a communal meal (such as a check to stretch limited rations into something satisfying or make a guest feel at ease over dinner), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Companionship": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>RO635 found SOP-II sitting alone in the cargo bay, knees pulled up, staring at nothing. She didn't ask what was wrong. She just sat down next to her, close enough that their shoulders touched.</em></p>
            <p><em>They stayed like that for a long time. Eventually, SOP-II leaned over until her head rested against RO's shoulder.</em></p>
            <p>"RO?"</p>
            <p>"Mm?"</p>
            <p>"Thanks for not asking."</p>
            <p>"Anytime."</p>
            <p><em>They sat in the cargo bay until the lights dimmed for the night cycle, and neither of them moved.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Your presence calms others. You have an intuitive sense for when someone needs company and when they need space, and people trust you instinctively because you make them feel seen.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to comfort, support, or simply be present for someone (such as a check to calm a panicking ally or convince someone they're not alone), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Contraband": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Mental",
      "Taboo"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The squad needed parts that didn't exist on the legal market anymore. Pre-war doll components, military-grade encryption modules, and a very specific caliber of ammunition that hadn't been manufactured in a decade. The broker listened to the list without expression.</em></p>
            <p>"I can get all of it. The components will take three days. The encryption modules, one week. The ammunition..." <em>She paused.</em> "That depends on whether you want it clean or whether you want it fast."</p>
            <p>"What's the difference?"</p>
            <p>"Clean means I source it through four intermediaries and nobody traces it back to you. Fast means I know a Varjager crew that has a crate of it and owes me a favor." <em>She smiled.</em> "Everything has a price, commander. My job is making sure you can afford it."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You always know where the black market operates in any settlement, and you can estimate the street value of any item or service. You have a network of contacts who deal in goods that don't officially exist.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving illicit trade (such as a check to locate a specific contraband item or negotiate a deal with a black market dealer), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Control": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Taboo"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The negotiation had gone exactly as she'd planned. Not because she was the most powerful person in the room (she wasn't), but because she'd spent three days before the meeting ensuring that every person at the table owed her something, feared something she knew, or wanted something only she could provide.</em></p>
            <p><em>The deal closed in her favor. She didn't smile. Smiling was for people who were surprised by outcomes.</em></p>
            <p>"You're terrifying," the commander said afterward.</p>
            <p>"I'm efficient. Terrifying is a side effect."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You need to be in command of every situation you enter. You can always identify the power dynamics in a room: who holds real authority, who is pretending, and what leverage exists to shift the balance.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to assert dominance or manipulate a situation to your advantage (such as a check to take command of a chaotic scene or maneuver someone into doing what you want), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Cosplay": {
    "type": [
      "Creative",
      "Physical"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p>"Careful, commander. You never know if the t-doll you're talking to is actually her, it might just be P90 in a really good costume."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You enjoy creating and wearing costumes, and can always identify the needed resources to create or replicate any costume you come across.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to disguise yourself (such as deception or performance), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Decorum": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Mental"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The commander tugged at his collar, scanning the crowded reception hall. Delegates from three PMCs and a government liaison milled about with drinks in hand. G36 materialized at his elbow.</em></p>
        <p>"Master. You are holding your glass in your dominant hand."</p>
        <p>"...So?"</p>
        <p>"Your dominant hand should remain free to offer handshakes. Additionally, your posture suggests you are about to lean against that pillar. You will not."</p>
        <p>"G36, I outrank everyone here."</p>
        <p>"And you will <em>continue</em> to, provided you do not disgrace yourself with a two-handed finger-food grip in front of the Minister of the Interior."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Formal society is your natural habitat. Etiquette, protocol, and all the subtle minutiae of diplomatic and professional conduct are second nature to you.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to ensure that you or your allies adhere to proper social protocol (such as a check to navigate a tense diplomatic reception or correct a faux pas before it causes an incident), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Drinking": {
    "type": [
      "Hedonic",
      "Social"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The mission was over. The squad was alive. A-91 produced a flask from somewhere on her person (nobody could ever figure out where she kept them all) and took a long pull.</em></p>
            <p>"A-91, it's 0900."</p>
            <p>"And we're alive. That's worth celebrating." <em>She offered the flask.</em> "Vodka. Good stuff, not that recycled coolant they sell in the Yellow Zone."</p>
            <p>"Where did you even get real vodka out here?"</p>
            <p><em>She tapped her nose and took another drink.</em> "A girl has her secrets, commander. And her priorities."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You always know where to find alcohol, no matter how remote or dry the location. You can identify the quality, origin, and approximate proof of any drink by taste alone.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving alcohol (such as a check to drink someone under the table or track down a source of liquor in an unfamiliar settlement), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Driving": {
    "type": [
      "Physical"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The road through the contamination zone was barely a road: cracked asphalt, collapsed overpasses, debris everywhere. The squad's transport had stalled twice already. Then Sakura climbed into the driver's seat, adjusted the mirrors, and put it in gear.</em></p>
            <p>"Sakura, are you sure about this? Your file says you have... bad luck."</p>
            <p>"With everything else, yes. Not with driving." <em>She threaded the transport through a gap between two wrecked cars that shouldn't have fit, without slowing down.</em> "Sakura Lucky Delivery had a one hundred percent completion rate across three contamination zones."</p>
            <p>"...And the 'Lucky' in the name?"</p>
            <p>"Aspirational."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You don't just enjoy speed, you understand the bond between driver and machine in motion. You know how to read a vehicle's limits and push them, whether in a race, a pursuit, or a desperate escape.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to push a vehicle to its limits (such as a check to weave through a dangerous obstacle course or coax a damaged transport through hostile terrain), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Fashion": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Creative"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The squad had thirty minutes before deployment. Most were doing final equipment checks. DSR-50 was adjusting her hair ribbon in a compact mirror.</em></p>
            <p>"DSR, we're about to drop into a combat zone."</p>
            <p>"And? Looking good and shooting straight aren't mutually exclusive." <em>She snapped the compact shut.</em> "Besides, have you seen what Springfield is wearing to the liaison dinner tonight? Someone has to uphold standards around here."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You always know the current trends in your region, and you can identify what is in vogue (and how to take advantage of that fact) in a new place after spending one or more scenes there.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to interact with clothes, jewelry, or other worn works of art (such as a check to assess someone's taste from their outfit or design a stunning ensemble), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Fortune-Telling": {
    "type": [
      "Reflective"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>Nemesis sat cross-legged on the deck of the Elmo, her prism catching the low light as she turned it slowly between her fingers. Krolik watched from a respectful distance. The commander did not.</em></p>
            <p>"Nemesis, I need the patrol route for tomorrow, not a horoscope."</p>
            <p>"The prism shows a forking of paths. One is bathed in amber: caution, but warmth. The other is silver: swift, but cold. The stars counsel patience."</p>
            <p>"Krolik, translate."</p>
            <p><em>Krolik sighed.</em> "She's saying take the southern route. It's slower but safer."</p>
            <p>"The prism has spoken," <em>Nemesis confirmed serenely.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can identify common portents and signs (stellar phenomena, patterns in nature, symbolic configurations, and other omens) along with their implications for the future, whether or not anyone else takes them seriously.</li>
                <li>After performing a check to discern the future (such as a check to perform a divination ritual or interpret signs and omens in your surroundings), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Gambling": {
    "type": [
      "Social",
      "Mental",
      "Thrill"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>Friday night at the café. The rifles were gathered around the corner table: Springfield, Lee-Enfield, Mosin-Nagant, WA2000. Five Card Stud. Springfield's face was as serene as ever.</em></p>
            <p>"I'll raise." <em>She pushed her chips forward with the same gentle precision she used to pour coffee.</em></p>
            <p>WA2000 slammed her cards down. "You're bluffing. You have to be bluffing. Nobody gets three hands in a row."</p>
            <p><em>Springfield smiled.</em> "Call me and find out."</p>
            <p><em>WA2000 did. Springfield was not bluffing. Springfield was never bluffing.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can always find a game wherever you go: cards, dice, fighting rings, or anything else people wager on. You have a keen eye for reading opponents and understanding odds.</li>
                <li>After performing a check involving games of chance or skill (such as a check to win a high-stakes poker hand or read an opponent's tells), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Gardening": {
    "type": [
      "Mental",
      "Reflective"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The rooftop of the Elmo wasn't designed for it, but someone had bolted planter boxes to the railing anyway. Colphne was up there most mornings, watering, pruning, murmuring to the plants in a way that made the other dolls uncomfortable.</em></p>
            <p>"Colphne, do the tomatoes actually grow faster when you talk to them?"</p>
            <p>"No. But I grow calmer when I talk to them, and calm hands make fewer mistakes with the pruning shears." <em>She held up a sprig of something green.</em> "Lemon balm. It shouldn't be able to grow at this latitude, but it doesn't seem to mind. Would you like some for your tea?"</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can always identify a plant by any of its parts, and you know its physical properties, including which are medicinal, which are poisonous, and which indicate environmental conditions like contamination.</li>
                <li>After performing a check related to plants or gardening (such as a check to identify a useful herb in the wild or cultivate something in difficult conditions), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Generosity": {
    "type": [
      "Interpersonal"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>Kalina set a small wrapped package on the commander's desk.</em></p>
            <p>"What's this?"</p>
            <p>"A gift for the liaison officer from the 3rd District. She collects antique fountain pens. This one's a 2038 Pelikan, pre-war manufacture, still has the original nib. I found it in a salvage lot marked for recycling."</p>
            <p>"...How do you know she collects fountain pens?"</p>
            <p><em>Kalina smiled in that way that meant the question would not be answered.</em></p>
            <p>"Just trust me, commander. This meeting is going to go very well."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can always identify a proper gift for a particular person that does not risk giving offense or sending the wrong message.</li>
