  },
  "Gossip": {
    "type": [
      "Social"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>Five-seveN leaned against the doorframe of the comms room, watching two dolls from another squad walk past, then turned back inside.</em></p>
            <p>"The tall one  (Recon Squad 3) has been filing extra maintenance requests. Three in two weeks."</p>
            <p>"So? Equipment wears out."</p>
            <p>"Not hers. She's filing them for someone in Squad 7. Someone she shouldn't even know well enough to do favors for." <em>Five-seveN's smile was razor-thin.</em> "Interesting, isn't it?"</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>At the start of each scene, you can always identify the character present who will know the juiciest rumors (besides yourself, obviously).</li>
                <li>After performing a check to spread or receive rumors (such as a check to cast someone in a certain light when telling a story about them or read people's current anxieties from the subtle ways they behave), you remove 3 strife.</li>
            </ul>
    """
  },
  "Gourmet": {
    "type": [
      "Mental",
      "Hedonic"
    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The squad stopped to rest in an abandoned settlement. While the others set up a perimeter, SPAS-12 had vanished into what remained of a convenience store. She emerged ten minutes later, cradling an armful of dusty cans and packets like they were made of gold.</em></p>
            <p>"SPAS, you don't need to eat."</p>
            <p>"That is the most depressing thing anyone has ever said to me." <em>She held up a dented tin.</em> "This is canned duck confit. Pre-war French import. And <em>this</em> is genuine black pepper, not that synthetic stuff they put in the ration packs."</p>
            <p>"You literally do not have a digestive system."</p>
            <p>"And yet I have <em>taste</em>, which is more than I can say for you. Give me fifteen minutes and a heat source."</p>
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can identify regional variations in cuisine and know a great deal about techniques of food preparation. You can always identify the ingredients in a dish, including those that are potentially dangerous.</li>
