    ],
    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The operative's hands were shaking again. Not badly. Not enough for anyone else to notice. He noticed.</em></p>
            <p><em>He found a quiet corner, away from the squad, and opened the small case in his breast pocket. Two ampoules. One for focus. One for calm. He'd told himself he'd only use them before missions. That was three months and a lot of missions ago.</em></p>
            <p><em>The needle went in clean. Two seconds later, the shaking stopped. The world snapped into focus: sharp, bright, manageable. He closed the case, tucked it away, and rejoined the squad with steady hands and clear eyes.</em></p>
            <p><em>Nobody noticed. That was the whole point.</em></p>
    """,
    "description": """
