    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The transport was wrecked. Comms were down. The contamination zone stretched in every direction, featureless and hostile. Most of the squad was panicking. The operative was already building a shelter from the wreckage.</em></p>
            <p>"What are you doing?"</p>
            <p>"The wind is coming from the northeast, which means the collapse dust will drift south. We set up on the leeward side of the wreck, use the hull as a windbreak. There's groundwater about two meters down, as you can tell from the soil color." <em>He was already digging.</em> "We have enough rations for three days if we half them. Rescue will come in two."</p>
            <p>"How do you know rescue will come in two?"</p>
            <p>"Because I activated the emergency beacon before I started digging. Priorities."</p>
