    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The Elmo had crossed into unfamiliar territory: a Yellow Zone settlement built inside the husk of a pre-war shopping mall. The squad was on edge. The operative who'd been riding with them for the past week stepped off the transport and stretched like she was coming home.</em></p>
            <p>"You've been here before?"</p>
            <p>"Never. But I've been to a dozen places like it." <em>She pointed.</em> "Market's on the second floor; always is, because the ground floor floods. Local authority will be whoever controls the generator. And that smell is lamb fat and rosemary, which means someone here trades with the Green Zone." <em>She grinned.</em> "New places aren't strange. They're just puzzles you haven't solved yet."</p>
