    "flavor": """
      <p><em>The intercepted message read: "The baker confirms the bread will rise on Thursday. Expect a warm delivery."</em></p>
            <p><em>The squad stared at it. The signals analyst smiled.</em></p>
            <p>"'Baker' is their handler, old Sangvis nomenclature. 'Bread rising' means an operation is escalating. 'Warm delivery' is armed personnel. They're launching on Thursday."</p>
            <p>"How do you get all that from a sentence about bread?"</p>
            <p>"Because language is never just language. Every word is a choice, and every choice tells you something about the person who made it." <em>She was already drafting a response in the same cipher.</em> "Now, do we want to warn them we're listening, or do we want to have some fun with this?"</p>
